claims:
7. A method of making activated carbon supported onto a monolith substrate, the method comprising:
      a) providing a monolith substrate; 
      b) providing a pitch; 
      c) coating the monolith substrate with the pitch; 
      d) oxidizing the pitch; 
      e) carbonizing the pitch when the softening point of the pitch is less than about 250° C.; and 
      f) activating the pitch to produce activated carbon.
